Random clues suddenly fit together

20
00:01:02.580 --> 00:01:06.510
Starting to make sense, oh, what's going on?

21
00:01:06.510 --> 00:01:12.980
Threads of time weaving into an intricate tapestry

22
00:01:13.070 --> 00:01:18.680
We can't stop the world from turning, it's changing along with every one of-

23
00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:21.250
US, US

24
00:01:21.870 --> 00:01:26.360
US, ALL OF US

25
00:01:30.110 --> 00:01:35.120
<b>Inside Pangaea Castle
The Holy Land, Mary Geoise</b>

26
00:01:38.080 --> 00:01:41.710
<b>The Attempted Murder
of a Celestial Dragon</b>

27
00:01:40.330 --> 00:01:41.710
Damn Revolutionary!

28
00:01:41.710 --> 00:01:43.710
Give back those keys!

29
00:02:24.830 --> 00:02:26.080
You're Sabo, right?!

30
00:02:26.080 --> 00:02:27.460
Huh?

31
00:02:27.460 --> 00:02:28.380
Aren't you...

32
00:02:28.750 --> 00:02:30.510
Jewelry Bonney?!

33
00:02:30.510 --> 00:02:33.260
You know me?
Good, that'll save us some time.

34
00:02:33.260 --> 00:02:35.760
I think we might be after the same thing.

35
00:02:37.010 --> 00:02:39.010
Intruders in the guards' quarters!

36
00:02:39.350 --> 00:02:41.520
They stole the keys to the slave collars!

37
00:02:41.520 --> 00:02:43.180
Apprehend them!

38
00:02:45.190 --> 00:02:47.860
I always heard Kuma had a daughter.

39
00:02:47.860 --> 00:02:51.530
I've been keeping tabs on the
Revolutionary Army for a while now.

40
00:02:51.530 --> 00:02:54.700
That's how I know I can trust you guys!

41
00:02:54.700 --> 00:02:56.530
Please, save my father!

42
00:02:56.530 --> 00:02:58.910
We will. That's why we're here.

43
00:03:02.910 --> 00:03:03.580
What?!

44
00:03:03.580 --> 00:03:04.410
Karasu!

45
00:03:04.410 --> 00:03:05.420
Yes.

46
00:03:05.420 --> 00:03:07.420
Take these keys!

47
00:03:07.420 --> 00:03:09.670
Tell Morley and the others...

48
00:03:09.670 --> 00:03:14.300
once you unlock the collars to Kuma
and the slaves, head straight back to headquarters.

49
00:03:14.300 --> 00:03:15.930
Your mission ends there!

50
00:03:20.260 --> 00:03:22.270
What about you, Sabo?

51
00:03:22.270 --> 00:03:24.180
Gotta take care of something first!

52
00:03:24.180 --> 00:03:26.350
Understood! Be careful!

53
00:03:32.400 --> 00:03:34.570
So what's your next move, Bonney?

54
00:03:35.070 --> 00:03:36.570
I'm going to Egghead!

55
00:03:36.570 --> 00:03:37.820
All by yourself?

56
00:03:38.200 --> 00:03:39.320
Yes!

57
00:03:39.700 --> 00:03:42.830
Sure you'll be all right?
That's World Government turf.

58
00:03:42.830 --> 00:03:47.330
I have to ask Vegapunk how
to restore my father's consciousness!

59
00:03:47.330 --> 00:03:49.330
It's the whole reason I set out to sea!

60
00:03:49.330 --> 00:03:53.090
Wait... are you telling me there's
a way to get Kuma back to normal?

61
00:03:53.590 --> 00:03:58.840
If there isn't already, I'll make him
figure something out! If he can't...

62
00:03:59.930 --> 00:04:01.350
There they are!

63
00:04:01.350 --> 00:04:02.430
This way!

64
00:04:02.430 --> 00:04:03.640
Hurry up!

65
00:04:13.320 --> 00:04:14.400
Where'd they go?!

66
00:04:14.400 --> 00:04:15.650
No one's here!

67
00:04:17.400 --> 00:04:18.910
How bizarre...

68
00:04:18.910 --> 00:04:20.620
I could've sworn I saw them...

69
00:04:21.070 --> 00:04:23.490
S-Sorry about that.

70
00:04:24.660 --> 00:04:29.290
I can't believe they reduced
the security in this tower again.

71
00:04:29.290 --> 00:04:33.040
Even though there's so much ground to cover.

72
00:04:33.040 --> 00:04:36.260
What? Don't you know?

73
00:04:36.260 --> 00:04:38.380
It's because of you-know-what.

74
00:04:38.380 --> 00:04:39.180
You-know-what?

75
00:04:40.430 --> 00:04:42.180
They saw, y'know, it.

76
00:04:42.180 --> 00:04:43.680
Saw what exactly?

77
00:04:43.680 --> 00:04:44.930
The Lost Chamber.

78
00:04:44.930 --> 00:04:47.680
You idiot! Don't even joke about that!

79
00:04:51.440 --> 00:04:52.360
Thanks.

80
00:04:52.360 --> 00:04:54.860
Egghead is in the New World.

81
00:04:54.860 --> 00:04:57.070
We're heading in the opposite direction.

82
00:04:57.400 --> 00:04:58.530
Be careful.

83
00:04:58.530 --> 00:04:59.320
Yeah.

84
00:04:59.860 --> 00:05:01.200
Best of luck to you.

85
00:05:03.320 --> 00:05:04.700
Man, this is freaky.

86
00:05:05.030 --> 00:05:05.950
Huh?

87
00:05:05.950 --> 00:05:08.370
Why are you being so nice to me?

88
00:05:08.370 --> 00:05:11.790
Pirates I get, but a Revolutionary?

89
00:05:12.710 --> 00:05:14.500
We both want to save Kuma.

90
00:05:14.500 --> 00:05:15.590
Yeah.

91
00:05:15.590 --> 00:05:17.300
Take care of my father!

92
00:05:20.550 --> 00:05:22.300
What would you like to ask us?

93
00:05:22.640 --> 00:05:26.390
Speak, King Cobra of Alabasta.

94
00:05:27.140 --> 00:05:28.350
Well...

95
00:05:28.770 --> 00:05:31.100
Where should I begin?

96
00:05:31.850 --> 00:05:35.520
History tells us that eight centuries ago,

97
00:05:35.520 --> 00:05:40.610
twenty monarchs came together
to found the World Government.

98
00:05:41.530 --> 00:05:44.410
As the creators of this new world,

99
00:05:44.410 --> 00:05:47.410
these monarchs relocated
their families to Mary Geoise,

100
00:05:47.740 --> 00:05:53.420
reigning over all thereafter
as the Celestial Dragons.

101
00:05:54.500 --> 00:05:59.420
Among themselves, the twenty treated
each other as equals, taking measures to ensure

102
00:05:59.880 --> 00:06:02.930
a sole monarch could
never subjugate the others.

103
00:06:03.260 --> 00:06:08.970
They intentionally erected an empty throne,
fencing it off with each of their weapons

104
00:06:08.970 --> 00:06:12.940
to symbolize that no one man
could sit above all others.

105
00:06:13.310 --> 00:06:17.020
Meanwhile, in the twenty countries
that lost their royal families,

106
00:06:17.020 --> 00:06:21.280
new monarchs were anointed
and have ruled ever since.

107
00:06:21.280 --> 00:06:25.990
Because of this, the names
of the First Twenty's royal families

108
00:06:25.990 --> 00:06:28.450
have been erased from their home countries.

109
00:06:28.950 --> 00:06:31.450
But Alabasta was different.

110
00:06:31.450 --> 00:06:37.380
Although Queen Nefertari Lili
was counted amongst the First Twenty,

111
00:06:37.380 --> 00:06:41.210
she chose to return to Alabasta,
rejecting the mantle of Celestial Dragon.

112
00:06:41.880 --> 00:06:46.260
As such, the Nefertari family
continues there to this day.

113
00:06:46.260 --> 00:06:52.020
For that reason, only nineteen weapons
surround the throne, technically speaking.

114
00:06:52.390 --> 00:06:54.520
All you have said is true.

115
00:06:54.520 --> 00:06:56.270
But what of it?

116
00:06:56.810 --> 00:07:00.780
Well, I've been poring over
Alabasta's oldest texts.

117
00:07:01.150 --> 00:07:09.280
Our only glimpses into the Void Century
are the books written in its aftermath.

118
00:07:09.620 --> 00:07:10.830
But I couldn't find her.

119
00:07:11.410 --> 00:07:13.290
Queen Lili wasn't mentioned once!

120
00:07:16.670 --> 00:07:20.800
You see, she never made it back to Alabasta.

121
00:07:21.380 --> 00:07:26.180
Thereafter, her younger brother
ruled the country in her stead.

122
00:07:27.260 --> 00:07:31.060
Is there anything you can tell me about her?

123
00:07:31.560 --> 00:07:33.310
Is that what you wanted to ask us?

124
00:07:33.720 --> 00:07:36.560
About some matter 800 years past?

125
00:07:37.060 --> 00:07:42.570
It is indeed true that Queen Nefertari Lili
alone chose to remain in her home country,

126
00:07:43.070 --> 00:07:47.070
but we were also under the impression
she had returned to Alabasta.

127
00:07:47.070 --> 00:07:49.660
Her reasoning and destination...

128
00:07:49.660 --> 00:07:54.080
Well, I'm afraid these things are lost to time.

129
00:07:54.080 --> 00:07:55.660
Apologies.

130
00:07:55.660 --> 00:07:56.790
We have no idea.

131
00:07:58.620 --> 00:08:00.670
Then... what is the D?

132
00:08:02.210 --> 00:08:04.510
Why are you asking that?

133
00:08:04.510 --> 00:08:09.260
In truth, she penned
a short letter 800 years ago.

134
00:08:10.010 --> 00:08:13.760
It has been passed down through
our royal family for generations.

135
00:08:17.520 --> 00:08:20.520
<b>Pangaea Castle</b>

136
00:08:20.520 --> 00:08:22.770
Stop! I'm begging you!

137
00:08:23.270 --> 00:08:24.530
Please!

138
00:08:25.150 --> 00:08:26.280
Please!

139
00:08:27.030 --> 00:08:28.650
You're hurting me!

140
00:08:28.650 --> 00:08:32.450
Somebody, I implore you! Help me!

141
00:08:34.950 --> 00:08:37.460
I did it! Father, I did it!

142
00:08:37.460 --> 00:08:39.710
I didn't give up,

143
00:08:39.710 --> 00:08:42.710
and I nabbed myself a giant mermaid!

144
00:08:43.710 --> 00:08:45.710
Well done, Charlos!

145
00:08:45.710 --> 00:08:48.420
Somebody, please help me!

146
00:08:48.420 --> 00:08:49.970
Oh no...

147
00:08:49.970 --> 00:08:52.090
My dear Princess Shirahoshi...

148
00:08:53.470 --> 00:08:55.470
Whatever should I feed you?

149
00:08:55.470 --> 00:09:00.850
From this day forth, you shall serve
as my personal steed into and around town!

150
00:09:00.850 --> 00:09:04.440
Shirahoshi is mine!

151
00:09:04.440 --> 00:09:06.860
Out of my way at once!

152
00:09:08.820 --> 00:09:11.110
This is exquisite!

153
00:09:12.660 --> 00:09:15.870
If you disobey me, I'll make you regret it!

154
00:09:16.240 --> 00:09:17.370
I refuse!

155
00:09:19.120 --> 00:09:21.870
Somebody, please!

156
00:09:22.210 --> 00:09:24.750
Somebody, please help me!

157
00:09:24.750 --> 00:09:26.210
Oh no!

158
00:09:26.210 --> 00:09:28.760
Daddy and our guards
are in the Conference Tower...

159
00:09:29.170 --> 00:09:30.550
Please!

160
00:09:30.550 --> 00:09:31.760
Somebody!

161
00:09:34.010 --> 00:09:35.760
We can't just stand by...!

162
00:09:37.010 --> 00:09:38.270
Please...

163
00:09:40.520 --> 00:09:42.270
Let's run the hell away!

164
00:09:42.270 --> 00:09:43.440
No!

165
00:09:43.440 --> 00:09:45.270
Hey, mermaid!

166
00:09:45.270 --> 00:09:47.570
I heard you defy me just now!

167
00:09:47.570 --> 00:09:49.030
Disobedient wench!

168
00:09:49.030 --> 00:09:52.400
Begging for our help?!
Honestly, how rude can you be?!

169
00:09:52.400 --> 00:09:55.910
It's not like she was gonna marry us anyway!

170
00:09:55.910 --> 00:09:56.910
Quite right!

171
00:09:56.910 --> 00:09:58.910
Who cares if that floozy survives?!

172
00:09:58.910 --> 00:10:00.160
Out of my way!

173
00:10:00.160 --> 00:10:03.420
Fools like you are as pliable as kelp!

174
00:10:04.420 --> 00:10:05.880
The Ryugu Kingdom!

175
00:10:07.840 --> 00:10:10.920
Don't defy them!
They'll destroy your whole country!

176
00:10:10.920 --> 00:10:11.920
Huh?!

177
00:10:13.180 --> 00:10:15.680
Sorry! We should've never
let you out of our sight!

178
00:10:15.680 --> 00:10:17.430
Brothers!

179
00:10:17.430 --> 00:10:19.180
Apologies for the wait!

180
00:10:19.180 --> 00:10:22.560
Now that we're here,
everything will be all right!

181
00:10:24.560 --> 00:10:26.060
Let's go home!

182
00:10:26.060 --> 00:10:28.320
We'll leave this dreadful place forever!

183
00:10:28.320 --> 00:10:30.070
Brother Fukaboshi...

184
00:10:30.070 --> 00:10:33.320
I agree. You three should go home.

185
00:10:33.650 --> 00:10:38.580
But the mermaid stays.
She's my newest pet, you see.

186
00:10:38.580 --> 00:10:41.830
Celestial Dragon scum!

187
00:10:41.830 --> 00:10:44.000
How dare you do that to our sister?!

188
00:10:45.580 --> 00:10:47.080
We'll make you pay!

189
00:10:49.840 --> 00:10:51.840
Get rid of them!

190
00:10:51.840 --> 00:10:54.590
Invincible Slave Kuma!

191
00:11:00.350 --> 00:11:02.600
Big Brother!

192
00:11:03.180 --> 00:11:04.850
Shirahoshi!

193
00:11:04.850 --> 00:11:06.190
Lady Rebecca!

194
00:11:06.190 --> 00:11:07.860
Don't worry! I'm coming!

195
00:11:07.860 --> 00:11:10.980
Rebecca! It's that man from before!

196
00:11:10.980 --> 00:11:13.490
How infuriating! I'll make him pay for this!

197
00:11:15.400 --> 00:11:16.990
Hey, Mjosgard!

198
00:11:16.990 --> 00:11:19.030
I can beat him up this time, right?!

199
00:11:19.030 --> 00:11:21.990
Certainly! I'll take full responsibility!

200
00:11:24.410 --> 00:11:27.710
The former Warlord of the Sea,
Bartholomew Kuma...!

201
00:11:27.710 --> 00:11:28.750
You have my pity!

202
00:11:28.750 --> 00:11:32.880
But it changes nothing! Forward, my brothers!

203
00:11:32.880 --> 00:11:33.510
– Right!
– Right!

204
00:11:33.510 --> 00:11:36.010
You have my permission to kill them, Kuma!

205
00:11:36.010 --> 00:11:40.010
They may be royals, but we
can just buy our way out of trouble!

206
00:11:40.010 --> 00:11:41.760
They're only fishmen after all!

207
00:11:41.760 --> 00:11:43.890
Damn you!

208
00:11:44.390 --> 00:11:45.730
Prince Fukaboshi!

209
00:11:45.730 --> 00:11:47.650
You must remember your station!

210
00:11:47.980 --> 00:11:49.150
Get out of my way!

211
00:11:49.150 --> 00:11:50.900
Leave it to them!

212
00:11:52.150 --> 00:11:55.530
What's the difference between
them and us, Mjosgard?!

213
00:11:55.530 --> 00:11:58.030
Look at how he's treating our sister!

214
00:11:58.030 --> 00:12:00.200
They can get away with it!

215
00:12:00.200 --> 00:12:03.040
As pirates, no nation is responsible for them!

216
00:12:04.080 --> 00:12:05.700
Mjosgard!

217
00:12:05.700 --> 00:12:09.040
I can't believe you struck me the other day!

218
00:12:09.040 --> 00:12:13.210
Kuma! Execute Mjosgard!

219
00:12:20.050 --> 00:12:22.180
Tontatta Combat...

220
00:12:22.180 --> 00:12:24.930
Eight-Impact Fist Secret
Technique: Drill Dragon...

221
00:12:24.930 --> 00:12:26.930
Sir Leo! Sir Sai!

222
00:12:26.930 --> 00:12:28.190
Don't do it!

223
00:12:28.190 --> 00:12:29.940
He's a Celestial Dragon!

224
00:12:30.850 --> 00:12:32.520
...Tail Hammer!

225
00:12:32.520 --> 00:12:33.980
...Nail!

226
00:12:41.120 --> 00:12:42.120
Charlos!

227
00:12:44.620 --> 00:12:46.250
They're doomed!

228
00:12:46.250 --> 00:12:48.250
He's dead for sure!

229
00:12:48.250 --> 00:12:50.750
This is murder!

230
00:12:50.750 --> 00:12:53.670
The murder of a Celestial Dragon!

231
00:12:53.670 --> 00:12:56.510
The Marine admirals are going to show up!

232
00:13:09.390 --> 00:13:12.730
No, Kuma-bear!

233
00:13:13.270 --> 00:13:19.280
It's okay now! You don't have
to listen to these bad men anymore!

234
00:13:19.280 --> 00:13:23.410
Let's go home together!

235
00:13:23.410 --> 00:13:24.910
What?!

236
00:13:24.910 --> 00:13:27.410
What is a giant doing here?!

237
00:13:27.790 --> 00:13:28.660
Morley!

238
00:13:28.660 --> 00:13:29.580
Karasu!

239
00:13:29.580 --> 00:13:31.420
I got the keys from Sabo!

240
00:13:31.420 --> 00:13:32.790
Who is that?!

241
00:13:32.790 --> 00:13:34.040
An intruder?!

242
00:13:34.040 --> 00:13:35.540
That's Morley!

243
00:13:35.540 --> 00:13:37.550
A commander of the Revolutionary Army!

244
00:13:37.550 --> 00:13:39.300
Okay! Going down!

245
00:13:45.470 --> 00:13:46.810
My darling boy!

246
00:14:02.200 --> 00:14:03.450
Esteemed Imu...!

247
00:14:03.450 --> 00:14:05.700
King Cobra is still here!

248
00:14:06.950 --> 00:14:08.450
Did he say "Imu"?!

249
00:14:23.430 --> 00:14:25.090
Lili...

250
00:14:28.560 --> 00:14:32.520
No one is supposed to sit there.

251
00:14:32.890 --> 00:14:37.310
No one man is allowed to bend
the world to their own will!

252
00:14:37.310 --> 00:14:44.410
I will answer two of your questions,
and you will answer one of my own, Cobra.

253
00:14:44.410 --> 00:14:46.370
Who in the world are you?!

254
00:14:48.160 --> 00:14:50.290
I know the name Imu.

255
00:14:50.830 --> 00:14:54.790
It must be a coincidence,
but among the First Twenty...

256
00:14:54.790 --> 00:14:56.830
Do not pry.

257
00:14:57.380 --> 00:14:59.000
I will not answer.

258
00:15:00.340 --> 00:15:03.380
But to answer your other questions...

259
00:15:04.340 --> 00:15:06.300
"D" is...

260
00:15:06.300 --> 00:15:10.140
the name of the people who once opposed us.

261
00:15:11.310 --> 00:15:15.100
In recent years, it has reared
its ugly head here and there...

262
00:15:15.100 --> 00:15:19.150
but these are mere echoes, ignorant
to even the meaning of their own names.

263
00:15:19.150 --> 00:15:21.530
And just like everything else,

264
00:15:21.530 --> 00:15:28.200
it stems from Queen Lili's
catastrophic blunder 800 years ago.

265
00:15:28.200 --> 00:15:29.240
Her blunder?

266
00:15:29.740 --> 00:15:34.710
Be it scholars researching the Void Century...

267
00:15:35.290 --> 00:15:40.790
or pirates hunting the poneglyphs
in search of treasure...

268
00:15:41.210 --> 00:15:44.670
If it weren't for Lili's mistake that fateful day,

269
00:15:45.340 --> 00:15:52.760
the loathsome artifacts known as poneglyphs
would not have been scattered all across the world.

270
00:15:57.730 --> 00:16:00.900
Given everything surrounding this past event...

271
00:16:00.900 --> 00:16:04.150
one cannot help but wonder.

272
00:16:04.860 --> 00:16:09.990
Was it truly a mistake that
the poneglyphs were unleashed?

273
00:16:09.990 --> 00:16:13.700
Or was it premeditated?

274
00:16:20.080 --> 00:16:21.710
The answer to that...

275
00:16:22.170 --> 00:16:26.420
must be recorded in
the letter Lili sent to Alabasta.

276
00:16:28.130 --> 00:16:35.600
This whole time, you've only referred
to her as Queen Nefertari Lili.

277
00:16:35.600 --> 00:16:36.850
Why is that?

278
00:16:38.480 --> 00:16:43.150
Speak the entire name
as it was signed on that letter.

279
00:16:51.160 --> 00:16:52.870
This is it.

280
00:16:52.870 --> 00:16:57.830
I don't think I'll be leaving this room alive.

281
00:17:01.210 --> 00:17:04.290
If I lied, I don't suppose
there's any chance you'd let me go?

282
00:17:04.290 --> 00:17:09.760
I'm afraid your fate was sealed
the moment you saw our Exalted Imu.

283
00:17:24.060 --> 00:17:25.940
He's right...

284
00:17:25.940 --> 00:17:28.320
It's the world's greatest taboo!

285
00:17:34.990 --> 00:17:37.080
What the hell is going on here?

286
00:17:37.080 --> 00:17:38.620
Something's clearly off.

287
00:17:40.210 --> 00:17:42.000
This is how it was signed.

288
00:17:43.040 --> 00:17:49.010
The queen of Alabasta, 800 years ago:

289
00:17:52.800 --> 00:17:54.970
Nefertari...

290
00:17:58.350 --> 00:17:59.890
D. Lili.

291
00:18:01.520 --> 00:18:03.100
"D"...

292
00:18:19.830 --> 00:18:20.910
Fire Fist!

293
00:18:25.920 --> 00:18:27.290
Rook Check!

294
00:18:31.920 --> 00:18:33.630
Where did you come from?!

295
00:19:02.700 --> 00:19:05.580
I was hoping I'd be able to take you all down,

296
00:19:05.960 --> 00:19:09.040
but I never thought I'd find
hell at the top of the world.

297
00:19:25.770 --> 00:19:27.520
Talk about depressing!

298
00:19:32.150 --> 00:19:33.360
You're...

299
00:19:33.360 --> 00:19:35.360
Luffy's...

300
00:19:35.780 --> 00:19:36.990
brother, right?

301
00:19:40.950 --> 00:19:43.330
You would help me?

302
00:19:43.330 --> 00:19:45.290
Despite being a Revolutionary?

303
00:19:46.160 --> 00:19:49.630
Our real fight is against
the people seated above the royals...

304
00:19:49.630 --> 00:19:50.960
These guys.

305
00:19:51.590 --> 00:19:53.260
But how do you know Luffy?

306
00:19:54.630 --> 00:19:56.840
He saved my life.

307
00:19:57.840 --> 00:19:59.680
That's so Luffy.

308
00:20:07.020 --> 00:20:09.270
Just keep it together!

309
00:20:09.270 --> 00:20:10.770
I'm getting you out of–

310
00:20:21.160 --> 00:20:23.910
Without me, you can make it.

311
00:20:23.910 --> 00:20:26.290
It's too late for me.

312
00:20:26.290 --> 00:20:27.410
Leave me behind!

313
00:20:27.410 --> 00:20:28.420
I'm saving you!

314
00:20:30.500 --> 00:20:33.130
I understand it now...

315
00:20:34.590 --> 00:20:37.920
I cannot permit you to die here!

316
00:20:37.920 --> 00:20:41.550
I need you to tell Luffy and Vivi...!

317
00:20:41.550 --> 00:20:43.260
Luffy and Princess Vivi?!

318
00:20:44.640 --> 00:20:47.730
Tell them that we share the moniker "D"!

319
00:20:47.730 --> 00:20:48.810
What?

320
00:20:53.770 --> 00:20:55.150
Is it a coincidence?

321
00:20:56.690 --> 00:20:58.400
Is what a coincidence?

322
00:20:58.400 --> 00:20:59.990
Well, both of you guys–

323
00:20:59.990 --> 00:21:01.620
They're done, they're done!

324
00:21:02.950 --> 00:21:04.370
They look so yummy!

325
00:21:04.370 --> 00:21:06.290
Hey! You can't take two at once!

326
00:21:06.290 --> 00:21:07.750
C'mon, I'm starving!

327
00:21:07.750 --> 00:21:09.710
But you can't–

328
00:21:11.000 --> 00:21:11.960
Yummy!

329
00:21:12.330 --> 00:21:13.960
Seriously, dude?

330
00:21:17.920 --> 00:21:19.930
Hey, it's really good!

331
00:21:19.930 --> 00:21:20.680
Sabo!

332
00:21:21.010 --> 00:21:22.890
You were just about to say something.

333
00:21:22.890 --> 00:21:24.050
Yeah.

334
00:21:24.050 --> 00:21:29.100
I wonder if it's a coincidence that
you both have a "D" in your name.

335
00:21:29.100 --> 00:21:30.270
"D"?

336
00:21:30.270 --> 00:21:33.860
Monkey D. Luffy and Portgas D. Ace.

337
00:21:33.860 --> 00:21:36.270
There's a "D" in both.

338
00:21:36.270 --> 00:21:38.280
Oh, guess you're right.

339
00:21:38.280 --> 00:21:40.610
Well, who gives a crap about names?

340
00:21:41.280 --> 00:21:43.910
Do you want a "D" too, Sabo?

341
00:21:43.910 --> 00:21:44.830
What?!

342
00:21:44.830 --> 00:21:45.950
Sa D. Bo!

343
00:21:45.950 --> 00:21:47.450
Why'd you put it there?!

344
00:21:47.450 --> 00:21:48.910
Does it really matter?!

345
00:21:48.910 --> 00:21:50.870
Sa D. Bo! Sa D. Bo!

346
00:21:59.710 --> 00:22:04.390
I finally see the path that Alabasta must take...

347
00:22:05.430 --> 00:22:07.310
Stay with me, King Cobra!

348
00:22:07.310 --> 00:22:08.930
Keep it together!

349
00:22:21.900 --> 00:22:22.990
King Cobra!

350
00:22:36.840 --> 00:22:37.920
King Cobra...!

351
00:22:40.010 --> 00:22:41.380
"The poneglyphs–

352
00:22:47.050 --> 00:22:49.510
"Bear the flag of the dawn..."

353
00:22:51.310 --> 00:22:54.440
"Nefertari D. Lili."

354
00:22:55.690 --> 00:22:57.270
I'm counting on you!

355
00:23:05.570 --> 00:23:07.950
I'm counting on you, Sabo!

356
00:23:11.040 --> 00:23:13.000
King Cobra!

357
00:23:17.080 --> 00:23:19.460
You must live on!

358
00:23:19.910 --> 00:23:25.000
Running so long, lost track of just how long it’s been

359
00:23:25.850 --> 00:23:32.360
Collected scars while striving, not even trying, beneath my skin

360
00:23:32.860 --> 00:23:39.780
But in the back of my head the dream is not dead, I remember a map

361
00:23:39.860 --> 00:23:46.070
to a treasure still gleaming, it’s within our grasp

362
00:23:46.210 --> 00:23:52.980
Can you feel my heart? Feelings I impart

363
00:23:52.940 --> 00:24:00.090
The promises are there; they're deep down but still primed to share

364
00:24:00.220 --> 00:24:09.200
Peerless dreams kept close, the dreams that always matter most

365
00:24:09.380 --> 00:24:14.960
Before we set sail why not raise a toast?

366
00:24:15.070 --> 00:24:21.980
So I pen this note to you! Dear sunrise, I’ll see you soon

367
00:24:22.140 --> 00:24:29.170
See the smile I saw the day that I sang this song to you

368
00:24:29.150 --> 00:24:36.220
And regardless of our age, these mem’ries will still remain

369
00:24:36.120 --> 00:24:43.330
Won’t forget until this wish makes it to you
